  "instructions": [
    "Combine water, zucchini, red bell pepper, and garlic in a pressure cooker.",
    "Close the lid and pressure-cook at 10 pounds per square inch (PSI) for 8 minutes.",
    "Let the pressure release naturally for 5 minutes before opening the lid.",
    "Stir in feta cheese, Greek yogurt, fresh dill, lemon juice, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Blend the mixture until smooth using an immersion blender.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional fresh dill if desired.",
    "Garnish with lemon wedges for added flavor and moisture."
